Package org.jtimer.Annotations

The package where all custom annotations are stored.

See: Description

  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    After
    Used to specificy that a method should run after each repetition of a time-loop.
    AfterClass
    Used to specify that a method should run at the beginning of all time-loops.
    Before
    Used to specificy that a method should run before each repetition of a time-loop.
    BeforeClass
    Used to specify that a method should run at the end of all time-loops.
    DisplayName
    Used to specify that you want to rename the graph item to something other than the method name.
    Settings
    A class level annotation that can be used to declare various settings that JTimer can read and do things depending on these settings.
    Time
    Used to specifiy that this method should be timed.
    Warmup
    Used to specify an amount of non-timed repetitions for the methods so that the CPU can warm up.

Package org.jtimer.Annotations Description

The package where all custom annotations are stored. These annotations are used to denote methods with various descriptors.
